key-EN.FSH.THRD.NO-ej.def: Fish species are based on Froese, R. and Pauly, D. (eds). 2008. Threatened species are the number of species classified by the IUCN as endangered, vulnerable, rare, indeterminate, out of danger, or insufficiently known.
key-EN.FSH.THRD.NO-ej.name: Fish species, threatened
key-EN.FSH.THRD.NO-ej.source: Froese, R. and Pauly, D. (eds). 2008. FishBase database, www.fishbase.org.

key-ER.FSH.CAPT.MT-ej.def: Capture fisheries production measures the volume of fish catches landed by a country for all commercial, industrial, recreational and subsistence purposes.
key-ER.FSH.CAPT.MT-ej.name: Fishery production, capture and aquaculture (metric tons)

key-IS.SHP.GOOD.TU-ej.def: Port container traffic measures the flow of containers from land to sea transport modes., and vice versa, in twenty-foot equivalent units (TEUs), a standard-size container. Data refer to coastal shipping as well as international journeys. Transshipment traffic is counted as two lifts at the intermediate port (once to off-load and again as an outbound lift) and includes empty units.
key-IS.SHP.GOOD.TU-ej.name: Container Port Traffic (TEU)

key-SL.TLF.ACTI.ZS-ej.def: Labor force participation rate is the proportion of the population ages 15-64 that is economically active: all people who supply labor for the production of goods and services during a specified period.
key-SL.TLF.ACTI.ZS-ej.name: Labor force participation rate, total (% of total population ages 15-64)
key-SL.TLF.ACTI.ZS-ej.source: International Labour Organization, ILOSTAT database. Data retrieved on June 15, 2021.

key-ohi-index-score-ej.def:
The Ocean Health Index is a decision-making tool and framework for conserving the human-ocean ecosystem because people need a healthy ocean. The Index is the first assessment tool that scientifically measures key elements from all dimensions of the ocean’s health — biological, physical, economic and social — to guide decision makers toward the sustainable use of the ocean.
Final OHI score that takes into account current status and predicted future status.
key-ohi-index-score-ej.name: Ocean Health Index
